{"questionId":"26442","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Leo is investigating whether a six-sided die is fair. He rolls the die <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn></math> times and records the&nbsp;observed frequencies in the following table:</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/ef136bc70fb66eaac3e9e958112f9dcce10d5359.png\"></p>\n<p>Leo carries out a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>χ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> goodness of fit test at a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo></math> significance level.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>-value for the test.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>(<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>-value <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo></math>)&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>287</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>28724163</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26442","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ1.7d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the p-value for the test.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}